\c 5
\s1 Adam's Descendants
\p
\v 1 This is the list of descendants of Adam:
\p When God created mankind, God made them so that they had many of the same attributes as Him.
\v 2 God created them as male and female, blessed them, and called them ‘mankind’.
\p
\v 3 Adam was aged 130 years when his third male child\f + \fr 5:3 \fk male child \ft In Hebrew it is clear from the story of each descendant that all listed in this genealogy are male children only. And this is similar in all genealogies of the Old Testament. Going forward from here, according to what is customary in Indonesian, the TSI will not specify the gender of every male child in the genealogical lists.\f* was born. Adam named that child Set. He had many similarities with Adam.
\v 4 After Set was born, Adam still lived for 800 years. During his life, Adam was the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 5 So Adam reached the age of 930 years.
\p
\v 6 Set was 105 when his son named Enos was born.
\v 7 After Enos was born, Set still lived 807 years. During his life, Set was the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 8 So Set reached the age of 912 years.
\p
\v 9 Enos was 90 years old when his son named Kenan was born.
\v 10 After Kenan was born, Enos lived on for 815 years. Throughout his life, Enos became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 11 So Enos reached the age of 905 years.
\p
\v 12 Kenan is 70 years old when his son named Mahalalel was born.
\v 13 After Mahalalel was born, Kenan was still alive for 840 years. Throughout his life, Kenan became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 14 So Kenan reached the age of 910 years.
\p
\v 15 Mahalalel was 65 years old when his son Jared was born.
\v 16 After he was born, Mahalalel lived for 830 years. Throughout his life, Mahalalel became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 17 So Mahalalel reached the age of 895 years.
\p
\v 18 Yared was 162 years old when his son Enoch was born.
\v 19 After Enoch was born, Jared lived for 800 years. Throughout his life, Jared became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 20 So Yared reached the age of 962 years.
\p
\v 21 Enoch was 65 years old when his son Metusalah was born.
\v 22 After Metulasah was born, Enoch lived in a close fellowship with God for 300 years. Throughout his life, Henok became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 23 So Enoch reached the age of for 365 years.
\v 24 Enoch lived in a close fellowship with God. One day he disappeared because God took him to heaven.
\p
\v 25 Methuselah was 187 years old when his son named Lamek was born.
\v 26 After Lamek was born, Methuselah still lived for 782 years. Throughout his life, Methuselah became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 27 So Methuselah reached the age of 969 years.
\p
\v 28 Lamek is 182 years old when his first child was born.
\v 29 Lamek named his son Noah because he said, “This son will bring relief\f + \fr 5:29 \fk relief \ft In Hebrew, the sound of the name ‘Noah’ is almost the same sound as the pronunciation of ‘relief’ or ‘ to comfort’.\f* in all the endeavors and hard work we have to do in order to produce food from the land that the LORD has cursed.”
\v 30 After Noah was born, Lamek was still alive for 595 years. Throughout his life, Lamek became the father of several other sons and daughters.
\v 31 So Lamek reached the age of 777 years.
\p
\v 32 From the time Noah was 500 years old he became the father of three sons, namely Shem, Japheth, dan Ham.\f + \fr 5:32 \fk the order of the descendants of Noah \ft TSI gives the names of Noah's descendants according to birth order. Literally the Hebrew text gives the order Shem, Ham, dan Japheth. But in Gen 9:24, Ham is clearly named as the youngest son of Noah. And in Gen. 10:21, it is written that Shem is the older brother of Japheth. TSI also uses the birth order in Gen. 6:10, 7:13, 9:18, and 10:1.\f*